The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Monday, May 7, 2007

IN POLITICS:
•	Pres. Bush Approval Edges Upward
•	With Race Just Begun, Giuliani, McCain and Clinton, Obama in Lead
•	Subdued N.J. Gov. Corzine Resumes Duties

IN THE NEWS:
•	Top Sunni: Make Changes by Next Week or Else
•	Trapped Survivor Found as Death Toll Rises to 12 after Kansas Storms

IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	How will France’s election of a pro-American president affect U.S. relations with Europe?
•	Two Democratic presidential hopefuls suggest moving U.S. troops from Iraq to Afghanistan. Is that a good idea?
•	When it comes down to it, would American voters elect another Republican president before they would elect a woman or a black?

